keywords","8265":"Selected topics","8266":"Selected placements","8267":"Selected audiences","8268":"Asset group status","8269":"Google Marketing Live","8270":"Video ads","8271":"AI summary","8272":"Let\'s start by creating...","10572":"compared to","11442":"Avg. CPV (TrueView)","11444":"Avg. Target CPA","11445":"Avg. Target ROAS","11448":"Conv. (by conv. time)","11450":"Conv. value (by conv. time)","11452":"Android Conversions","11453":"Android Conv. rate","11454":"Android conv. value","11455":"Extrapolated conversions","11456":"Local competitive clicks","11457":"Local competitive store visits","11458":"All views","11462":"Mobile speed score","11463":"Mobile-friendly click rate","11464":"Valid AMP click rate","11465":"View rate (TrueView)","11473":"Client account cost / conv.","11474":"“Average cost-per-click (CPC)” is the amount you\'ve paid for your ad divided by its total clicks. If your ad receives 2 clicks, one costing \$0.20 and one costing \$0.40, your average CPC for those clicks is \$0.30.","11475":"Average cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM) is the average amount that you\'ve been charged for 1,000 impressions.","11476":"TrueView average cost-per-view (previously called average cost-per-view) is the average amount you’ve been charged for TrueView views of this campaign. It equals the total cost divided by the total number of TrueView views.","11477":"“Average impression frequency per user (7 days)” is the average number of times a unique user was shown an ad from your campaign. For each day in your selected date range, this metric takes into account the past 7 days and shows the average frequency for those days.Use this metric to better understand how frequently a person was shown your ad within a 7-day period.","11478":"When someone clicks your ad, it\'s counted here.\\nThis metric is accredited by the Media Rating Council (MRC) in desktop and mobile environments for the Search and Display Networks.","11479":"“Click share” is the clicks you\'ve received on the Search Network divided by the estimated maximum number of clicks that you could have received.\\n\\nHow often your product is clicked depends on your ads\' targeting settings, budget, approval statuses, bids, and the quality of your product data.","11480":"“Position above rate” is how often another advertiser’s ad in the same auction shows in a higher position than your own, when both of your ads were shown at the same time.","11481":"“Conversions” shows the number of conversions you received after ad interactions (such as text ad clicks or video ad views).\\n\\nThe conversion settings “Include in ‘Conversions,’” “Count,” and “Include cross-device conversions” affect the number you see here.","11482":"“Conv. rate” shows how often, on average, an ad interaction leads to a conversion. It’s “Conversions” divided by the interactions with your ad.\\n\\nAd interactions include clicks for text ads and views for video ads. This metric only includes interactions that could lead to conversions.","11483":"“Conversion value” is the sum of conversion values for your conversions. This metric is useful only if you entered a value for your conversion actions.","11484":"Cost is the sum of your spend during this period","11485":"“Cost per conversion (“Cost/conv.”)” shows the average cost of a conversion. It’s your cost divided by your conversions.\\n\\nIf you track multiple conversion actions, your overall cost per conversion may be lower than the cost for each conversion action.\\n\\nThe cost in this metric only includes ad interactions that could lead to conversions.","11486":"“Clickthrough rate (CTR)” measures how often people click your ad after it\'s shown to them, which can help you understand the effectiveness of your ad.\\n\\nCTR is calculated by dividing the number of clicks your ad receives by the number of times your ad is shown. If you have 5 clicks and 1000 impressions, then your CTR is 0.5%.","11487":"“Android conversions” shows the number of android conversions you received after ad interactions (such as text ad clicks or video ad views).","11488":"“Android conversion rate” shows how often, on average, an ad interaction leads to a conversion. It’s “Android conversions” divided by the interactions with your ad.","11489":"“Android conversion value” is the sum of conversion values for your android conversions. This metric is useful only if you entered a value for your android conversion actions.","11490":"An earned view occurs when someone views your video ad, then later watches another video on your linked YouTube channel, within 7 days of the initial view.\\n\\nYou aren\'t charged for earned views. Multiple views from the same person are counted as a single earned view.","11491":"An engagement occurs when a consumer engages with an ad, for example, expanding a Lightbox ad or a card on a video ad, or viewing or clicking a Showcase Shopping ad. Engagements can help you understand how well your ad is performing. Relevant, highly-targeted ads with attractive content can encourage viewers to engage more deeply with your brand.","11492":"An impression is counted each time your ad is served on Google\'s ad networks, such as on Google.com, YouTube, or other publisher websites and apps. Impressions help you understand how often your ad is being seen.","11493":"“Impression share” is the number of impressions you received divided by the estimated number of impressions you were eligible to receive.\\n\\nEligibility is based on your current ads\' targeting settings, approval statuses, bids, and Quality Scores. This number is updated once a day.","11494":"An interaction is the main action associated with an ad format. These include clicks for text and Product Shopping ads, views for video ads, and more.\\n\\nInteractions help determine whether your ads are meeting your performance goals.","11495":"“Interaction rate” measures how often people interact with your ad after it\'s shown to them. This helps measure your ad\'s effectiveness.","11496":"The number of clicks on other advertisers\' ads where you didn\'t show a competing ad.\\n\\nThis is only on local search queries that are relevant to you.","11497":"The number of visits to other advertisers\' physical stores (after an ad click) where you didn\'t show a competing ad.\\n\\nThis is only on local search queries that are relevant to you.","11498":"“Outranking share” is how often your ad ranked higher in the auction than another advertiser’s ad, or if your ad showed when theirs did not.","11499":"“Overlap rate” is how often another advertiser’s ad received an impression in the same auction that your ad also received an impression.","11500":"Phone calls are the number of times people clicked on a phone number displayed in an ad on a mobile device or manually dialed the Google forwarding number displayed in an ad on any device.","11501":"“Top of page rate” is how often your ad (or the ad of another advertiser, depending on which row you\'re viewing) was shown at the top of the page in search results.","11502":"Conv. value/cost, or Return-on-ad-spend (ROAS), measures your return on investment. It’s the conversion value divided by total cost of all ad interactions.\\n\\nCost here doesn’t include interactions that can’t lead to conversions, such as those that happen when you aren’t using conversion tracking.","11503":"“Search impression share” is the impressions you’ve received on the Search Network divided by the estimated number of impressions you were eligible to receive.\\n\\nEligibility is based on your current ads\' targeting settings, approval statuses, bids, and quality. Impression share data is updated daily.","11504":"Mobile speed score is a measure of how quickly your page loads after clicks on your mobile ads. The score is a range from 1 to 10, 10 being fastest.","11505":"“Store visits” is the number of times people visited a store after clicking an ad for that advertiser.","11506":"Mobile-friendly click rate is the percentage of mobile clicks on the Search Network that go to a mobile-friendly page.\\n\\nA page\'s mobile friendliness is determined by Google\'s Mobile-Friendly test. This data may be up to 14 days old. If you\'ve made recent updates to one of your pages, you should wait up to 14 days for those changes to be reflected in this column.","11507":"Valid AMP click rate is the percentage of ad clicks to AMP landing pages that reach a valid AMP page, as determined by the AMP Validator. This column only measures clicks from the Google search results page.","11508":"Unique users shows the total number of people who saw an ad in Display or Video campaigns over a given time period.\\n\\nHow it works: This metric uses cross-device statistical models to measure the total reach of an ad by adjusting for cases when people may see the same ad on different devices or when multiple people share one device. These models are calculated at the country level.","11509":"TrueView view rate (previously called view rate) measures the percentage of people who watched a significant portion of your video ad, or clicked or tapped on it. It equals the number of TrueView views divided by the number of impressions.","11510":"A TrueView view (previously called a view) is counted when someone chooses to watch or engage with your video ad instead of skipping or scrolling past it. ","11522":"“Client account conversions” shows the number of conversions you received after ad interactions (such as text ad clicks or video ad views).\\n\\nIncluded conversions are determined by external accounts.","11523":"“Conversions” shows the number of conversions you received after ad interactions (such as text ad clicks or video ad views).\\n\\nThe “Include in ‘Conversions’” setting for each action determines if the action\'s conversions are included here.\\n\\nSearch Ads 360 Smart Bidding optimizes the conversions in this column","11524":"Conv. value/cost measures your return on investment. It’s the conversion value divided by total cost of all ad interactions.\\n\\nCost here doesn’t include interactions that can’t lead to conversions, such as those that happen when you aren’t using conversion tracking.","11525":"Conv. value/cost measures your return on investment. It’s the value of the conversions in the “Conversions” column divided by the total cost of all ad interactions.\\n\\nCost here doesn’t include interactions that can’t lead to conversions, such as those that happen when you aren’t using conversion tracking.","11526":"“Conv. rate” shows how often, on average, an ad interaction leads to a conversion. It’s “Client account conversions” divided by the interactions with your ad.\\n\\nAd interactions include clicks for text ads and views for video ads. This metric only includes interactions that could lead to conversions.","11527":"“Conversion value” is the sum of conversion values for the conversions included in the “Conversions” column. This metric is useful only if you entered a value for your conversion actions.","11528":"“Cost per conversion (Cost/conv.)” shows the average cost of the conversions included in the “Conversions” column. It\'s your cost divided by your conversions.\\n\\nIf you track multiple conversion actions, your overall cost per conversion may be lower than the cost for each conversion action.\\n\\nThe cost in this metric only includes ad interactions that could lead to conversions.","11529":"Phone calls are the number of times people clicked on a phone number displayed in an ad on a mobile device or manually dialed the Google forwarding number displayed in an ad on any device.\\n\\nApplicable only to Google Ads","11530":"“Average cost-per-action (“Avg. CPA”)” shows the average cost of a conversion. It’s your cost divided by your conversions.\\n\\nIf you track multiple conversion actions, your overall cost per conversion may be lower than the cost for each conversion action.\\n\\nThe cost in this metric only includes ad interactions that could lead to conversions.","11531":"Return-on-ad-spend (ROAS) measures your return on investment. It’s the conversion value divided by total cost of all ad interactions.\\n\\nCost here doesn’t include interactions that can’t lead to conversions, such as those that happen when you aren’t using conversion tracking."}');
